How to perform SAGE mapping (via LocusLink for known genes and via
UniGene for novel genes)

a) extract UniGene LocusLink mapping from
   an NCBI's file describing all UniGene clusters (Hs.data.Z from
   ftp://ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/schuler/unigene)

- download and call unigene.dat
- perl unigene_locuslink_extractor.pl > unigene_locuslink.dat

b) join that with enst_locuslink.dat mapping (a table from Ensembl
dumped by Arek) and SAGEmap_ug_tag-rel-Nla3-Hs.zip (download from NCBI's
SAGE
ftp://ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/sage/map/Hs/Nla3/) using ELUSmapper.pl to
produce
ELUSmapper.dat

c) Use perl ENSUmapper.pl for direct mapping
   of Ensembl transcripts to UniGene clusters
   (chromosome names in chr.dat)

d) ENSUpostprocessor.pl     cut-off 300 bits, eliminate UniGenes mapping
                            to more than 15 ENSTs
e) ELUS_ENSUjoiner.pl       join ELUS and ENSU mapping - use ENSU mapping
                            only if there is no ELUS mapping       

Tests:
ELUS_ENSUtester.pl - compare mapping for known genes (ELUS vs ENUS
mapping)
test_genes         - hand check for my favourite genes

